main event: Three unidentified objects were observed near Waterloo, Iowa on September 17, 1955.
interesting points: The objects appeared as stars, alternating between white, red, and green colors.
The objects were stationary and faded out.
The objects were compared to a previous sighting in LeGrand, Iowa on September 4, 1955.
Three witnesses observed a disk-like object making a zigzag motion, approximately 6-8 feet in diameter, and moving too fast to measure exactly.
The disk-like object disappeared into the clouds.
sighted object: three unidentified objects and a disk-like object
